// C2: Acting Components
instance PermanentMagnetSynchronousMotor : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Permanent magnet synchronous motor coupled with cycloidal gear for the first vertical axis of MABI MAX 100 industrial robot. Accepts position, speed, or acceleration control inputs within defined mechanical and safety limits."
]

instance CycloidalGearbox : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Cycloidal gearbox integrated with the permanent magnet synchronous motor to enable precise motion regulation of the first vertical axis. Operates within safety-constrained mechanical limits."
]

// C3: Physical sensing components
instance MotorShaftEncoder : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "High-resolution position encoder mounted directly on the motor shaft of the first vertical axis, providing sub-millimeter precision positional feedback."
    DTDFVocab:producedData MotorShaftPositionData
]

instance GearboxPositionEncoder : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Secondary high-resolution position encoder positioned behind the cycloidal gearbox, providing synchronized rotational position feedback for the first vertical axis."
    DTDFVocab:producedData GearboxPositionData
]

// C4: Physical-to-virtual interaction
instance MotorShaftPositionData : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom MotorShaftEncoder
    base:desc "Time-series positional data streamed from the motor shaft encoder via MQTT protocol, representing high-resolution rotational position measurements."
]

instance GearboxPositionData : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom GearboxPositionEncoder
    base:desc "Time-series positional data streamed from the gearbox encoder via MQTT protocol, representing synchronized rotational position measurements after gear reduction."
]

instance CombinedAxisPositionData : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom MotorShaftEncoder, GearboxPositionEncoder
    base:desc "Aggregated time-series data combining motor shaft and gearbox encoder measurements to enable comprehensive friction and mechanical behavior analysis of the first vertical axis."
]

// C10: Models/Data
instance FrictionBehaviorModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Executable friction behavior simulation model created in MathWorks MATLAB Simulink, integrating sensor data to validate and analyze mechanical dynamics of the first vertical axis."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo SimulinkExecutionEnvironment
]

instance AxisPositionData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Processed and aggregated time-series positional data from both encoders, normalized and filtered for friction analysis. Includes derived metrics like velocity and acceleration."
    DTDFVocab:fromData CombinedAxisPositionData
    DTDFVocab:inputTo SimulinkExecutionEnvironment, DataVisualizationDashboard
]

instance RobotAxisMechatronicModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "SysML-based mechatronic model representing the structural and behavioral relationships between mechanical, electrical, and control subsystems of the first vertical axis."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo SysMLModelingEnvironment
]

// C11: Enablers
instance MQTTStreamingProtocol : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Message Queuing Telemetry Transport (MQTT) protocol enabling low-latency, bidirectional streaming of time-series sensor data from physical robot to digital shadow."
    DTDFVocab:enables LiveDataAcquisitionService, DataAggregationService
]

instance SimulinkExecutionEnvironment : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "MathWorks MATLAB Simulink environment providing executable simulation capabilities for friction behavior modeling and validation."
    DTDFVocab:enables FrictionAnalysisService, SimulationValidationService
]

instance SysMLModelingEnvironment : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Systems Modeling Language (SysML) environment for creating and managing multi-abstraction models of the robot's mechatronic architecture."
    DTDFVocab:enables ModelBasedDesignService
]

instance DataVisualizationDashboard : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Dashboard-based interface providing real-time and historical visualization of sensor data and simulation results for operational insights."
    DTDFVocab:enables DataMonitoringService, AnomalyDetectionService
]

// C6: Services
instance LiveDataAcquisitionService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Real-time streaming service collecting and transmitting time-series sensor data from the robot's first axis via MQTT protocol."
    DTDFVocab:provides RealTimePositionInsight
]

instance DataAggregationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service processing, aggregating, and abstracting raw sensor traces into contextualized datasets for specific analytical purposes."
    DTDFVocab:provides ProcessedPositionDataInsight
]

instance FrictionAnalysisService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service executing friction behavior simulations using MathWorks MATLAB Simulink to analyze mechanical dynamics of the first vertical axis."
    DTDFVocab:provides FrictionBehaviorInsight
]

instance SimulationValidationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service validating physical dynamics through simulation-model comparisons, enabling offline analysis to improve control strategies."
    DTDFVocab:provides ModelValidationInsight
]

instance DataMonitoringService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service providing real-time visualization of sensor data and performance metrics through dashboard interfaces."
    DTDFVocab:provides OperationalTrendInsight
]

instance AnomalyDetectionService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service analyzing historical and real-time data to detect performance anomalies in the first vertical axis."
    DTDFVocab:provides AnomalyDetectionInsight
]

instance ModelBasedDesignService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Service managing SysML-based multi-abstraction models of the robot's mechatronic architecture across requirements, functional, and logical layers."
    DTDFVocab:provides SystemArchitectureInsight
]

// C17: Insights/Actions
instance RealTimePositionInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Continuous monitoring of the first vertical axis's positional accuracy in real-time, enabling immediate operational awareness."
]

instance ProcessedPositionDataInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Aggregated and normalized positional data with derived metrics (velocity, acceleration) for friction analysis and performance optimization."
]

instance FrictionBehaviorInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Detailed analysis of friction characteristics in the first vertical axis, identifying wear patterns and mechanical inefficiencies."
]

instance ModelValidationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Validation results comparing simulation models with actual physical behavior to assess model fidelity and identify discrepancies."
]

instance OperationalTrendInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Historical performance trends of the first vertical axis, enabling predictive maintenance and optimization recommendations."
]

instance AnomalyDetectionInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Identified anomalies in sensor data or performance metrics indicating potential mechanical issues or control system failures."
]

instance SystemArchitectureInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Structural and behavioral relationships between mechanical, electrical, and control subsystems of the first vertical axis as modeled in SysML."
]

instance twinning_time_scale : DTDFVocab:TimeScale [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system operates within a temporal framework defined by the **automated one-way data flow** between the physical object and its digital representation, as described in the Digital Shadow Reference Model. While the document does not specify exact synchronization frequencies or latency requirements, it implies a **real-time, data-driven representation** where sensor data (e.g., from robot axes) is collected as **time series** and aggregated for specific purposes. The system's temporal granularity is tied to the **contextual data traces** captured over defined intervals, ensuring alignment between the physical state and its digital abstraction. No explicit mention of multi-scale time handling (e.g., microseconds for control vs. minutes for analytics) or service-specific time constraints (e.g., hard real-time vs. soft real-time) is provided in the document."
]

instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The **Digital Twin constellation** is implicitly addressed through **Model-Based Systems Engineering (MBSE)** frameworks, which rely on **architecture description languages (ADLs)** (e.g., ACME, AADL, MontiArc, SysML IBDs) to define component-based systems with interfaces, interconnections, and composition. Behavioral descriptions are extended via tools like **MathWorks Simulink**, simulation methods, or general-purpose languages (C++, Java). The **Digital Shadow Reference Model** (Fig. 1) focuses on passive data aggregation, but the broader **Digital Twin system** requires **active components** (e.g., autonomous processing units) to interpret and act on data, as highlighted by Kritzinger et al. [32]–[37]. Orchestration and coordination are not explicitly detailed, but the integration of **multiple modeling notations and tools** (e.g., SysML, ADLs, simulation tools) suggests a **heterogeneous, modular architecture** with potential for **resource management** via component-based orchestration patterns. No explicit mention of system-wide coordination mechanisms (e.g., middleware, event-driven architectures) is provided."
]

instance dt_technical_connection : DTDFVocab:TechnicalConnection [
    base:desc "The **dt_technical_connection** for the Digital Shadow system is primarily defined by a **one-way communication architecture** leveraging the **MQTT protocol** for streaming sensor data from physical assets to the digital representation. The document does not specify the **network topology** (e.g., star, mesh, or hierarchical) or **bandwidth/latency requirements**, though the use of MQTT suggests support for **low-bandwidth, high-frequency data transmission** typical in IoT deployments. No details are provided on **reliability mechanisms** (e.g., retransmission policies, QoS levels) or **security protocols** (e.g., TLS, authentication/authorization frameworks). The connection is inherently **unidirectional**, with no bidirectional or control-oriented communication pathways described."
]

instance horizontal_integration : DTDFVocab:HoriIntegration [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system integrates with external systems via **sensor data streaming protocols**, specifically **MQTT**, as referenced in the context of manufacturing use cases (e.g., robot axes). The document does not provide explicit details on **interoperability standards** (e.g., OPC UA, REST APIs) or **data exchange formats** (e.g., JSON, XML), but it confirms the use of **lightweight, publish-subscribe messaging** for real-time data acquisition. Dependencies on **enterprise systems** (e.g., ERP, MES) are not mentioned; instead, the focus is on **heterogeneous modeling tools** (e.g., SysML, Simulink) and **stakeholder perspectives** during the development phase. No explicit patterns for **cross-Digital Twin integration** (e.g., federated twins) or **enterprise system dependencies** are described."
]

instance standardization : DTDFVocab:Standardization [
    base:desc "The provided context does not explicitly mention **industry standards** or **specifications** for Digital Twin (DT) systems. However, the **Model-Based Systems Engineering (MBSE)** framework leverages **SysML** (ISO/IEC 10746-5:2011) as a standardized modeling language for system architecture and behavior. **Architecture Description Languages (ADLs)** like **AADL** (SAE AS5506) and **ACME** are also standardized for component-based system modeling. **Interoperability** is implied through the integration of **heterogeneous tools** (e.g., Simulink, C++, Java) and **multi-notation models**, though no explicit **compliance frameworks** (e.g., ISO 23247 for DTs) or **certification requirements** are referenced. The **Digital Shadow Reference Model** (Fig. 1) does not address standardization beyond its UML-based conceptualization."
]

instance security_and_safety_considerations : DTDFVocab:SecuritySafety [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system incorporates **physical safety measures** through the **safety cell of the MABI MAX 100 robotic arm**, which restricts its maximum working range to **[-90°, 90°]** to prevent collisions or unsafe operations. **Communication security** is addressed via **MQTT (Message Queuing Telemetry Transport)** for streaming time-series sensor data, ensuring lightweight and efficient data exchange between components. However, the provided documents do **not specify** explicit cybersecurity protocols (e.g., encryption, authentication, or access control mechanisms), threat mitigation strategies, fail-safe mechanisms, or compliance with safety-critical standards (e.g., ISO 26262, IEC 61508)."
]